OL,6,FAt the Court of Appeal on Tuesday, her
OL,7,Fbarrister said the sentence was
OL,8,F"manifestly excessive" and should be
OL,9,Freduced, stating that the case
OL,10,Fconcerned a "lapse of concentration".
OL,12,FThree senior judges ruled that
OL,13,FCurtis's sentence was "manifestly
OL,14,Fexcessive" and reduced it to one of
OL,15,Fthree years, while increasing her
OL,16,Fdisqualification from driving from six
OL,17,Fyears to seven-and-a-half years.
